Useful Stuff
=============
cd /bin
curl https://github.com/git/git/raw/master/contrib/completion/git-completion.bash -OL
source git-completion.bash



lynx -source rawgit.com/transcode-open/apt-cyg/master/apt-cyg > apt-cyg
install aptâ€”cyg /bin
apt-cyg install nano



vim ~/.bashrc
alias desktop="cd C:/Users/huyle/Desktop"
alias open='cygstart'
alias reload='source ~/.bash_profile'
export PATH="${HOME}/bin:${PATH}"



Tabs and Hotkeys
================
We'll use Console2 :  https://sourceforge.net/projects/console/
https://sourceforge.net/projects/console/files/latest/download

Integrate with Command Prompt

For 64 bit, add C:\cygwin64\bin; to the end (System -> PATH ) of the environment variables.



==========================
Can you answer the 10 most popular Linux tech job interview questions?

	 How to check the kernel version of a Linux system?
		UName 	-a
				-v
				-r

	 How to see the current IP address on Linux?
		ifconfig
		ip addr show eth0

	 How to check for free disk space in Linux?
		df -ah

	 How to see if a Linux service is running?
		service serviceName status
			serviceName statr/running, process 286
		systemctl status serviceName

	 How to check the size of a directory in Linux?
		ls
			du -sh directoryName

	 How to check for open ports in Linux?
		sudo netstat -tulpn

	 How to check Linux process information (CPU usage, memory, user information, etc.)?
		ps aux | grep nginx
		top
		htop

	 How to deal with mounts in Linux
		ls /mnt
		mount /dev/sda2 /mnt
		mount
		less /etc/fstab

	 Man pages
		man <command>
		man ps

	 Other resources
